The paper deals with face detection and analysis using a fully convolutional neural network, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques for classification and regression tasks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of affective computing, which is a subfield of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper deals with facial attributes and smile detection, which are common topics in multimedia (cs.MM).
